        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 10:44PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 1044 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 22
miles northeast of Alzada, or 46 miles southeast of Ekalaka, moving
east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Albion.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
